      {"LFM %instance% %difficulty%, need a %role%. %gearscore%+ and bring %consumable%.", "Summon from %city%?", "Aye, soon as we've a %class% for the last slot.", "On my way. Don't pull %boss% without me, I mean it."},
      {"Is it worth grinding %rep% all the way to exalted?", "Depends. The %mount% at the end is worth more than %gold% to the right buyer.", "Sold. I'll start the %profession% dailies this %timeofday%.", "Pace yourself. That rep broke better folk than us."},
      {"Camped %zone% for %rare% three nights running.", "Still nothing?", "Nothing but %weather% and regret.", "It'll spawn the moment you log to sleep. They always do.", "...you're right and I hate it."},
      {"Bard at %shop% is taking requests.", "Ask for the ballad of %tale%.", "Too sad for a %season% night, surely.", "That's exactly why. A good dirge and a warm pint — best %timeofday% you can buy.", "...go on then. Make us weep into the ale."},
      {"A %race% %class% just walked in wielding %item%.", "The real one?", "Glows like a dropped star. Either it's real or it's the best forgery in %city%.", "Buy them a drink and find out. Subtly.", "There is nothing subtle about you."},
      {"How'd the %instance% run go?", "We wiped on %boss% six times, then a %class% dropped %spell% and it just... clicked.", "%difficulty%?", "%difficulty%. We were underleveled and overconfident.", "The two great traditions of this realm. Drinks on me."},
      {"Took %route% out to %zone% for the %event% festivities.", "Worth the trip?", "%weather% the whole way, but the lanterns at the end? Worth every copper.", "And the %gold% you spent on trinkets, no doubt.", "...the festival economy is a predator and I am its prey."},
    },
    -- group discussions (many voices, rotating cast of 4-6)
    groups = {
      {"Settle it for me: which capital is the finest in all Azeroth?", "Ironforge. Warm stone, endless ale, and the Great Forge never goes cold.", "Stormwind. Spires like they're carved from morning light. Nothing finer.", "Darnassus, easily. You've clearly never lost an hour to moonlight on the ponds.", "Thunder Bluff. Open sky, clean wind, and not a single auctioneer screaming in your ear.", "Silvermoon. Ten thousand years of refinement, and it shows in every gilded arch.", "Undercity, if you've the stomach. Grim, yes, but the Forsaken made a home out of grief.", "You're all wrong. Booty Bay. No rules, great fishing, and the ale's only mostly poisoned.", "...of course the goblin lover says Booty Bay.", "It has a SUNSET over the SEA. What's your spire got? Pigeons.", "Every one of you is loyal to wherever your hearthstone's set. Admit it.", "Fair. Home's home. Mine just happens to be the prettiest."},
      {"Anyone else feel the cities are quieter since the call-up north?", "Half the regulars from my tavern shipped to Icecrown. Place feels hollow.", "The recruiting officers are at every gate. Argent Crusade, mostly.", "My brother signed on. Said someone has to. I couldn't argue.", "Noble cause. Terrible odds. The Scourge doesn't tire and doesn't grieve.", "They say Fordring himself is leading the push. If anyone can, it's him.", "I just hope the ones who go come back. Most of them. Some of them.", "Light keep them. Earth Mother hold them. Whatever you pray to, pray it loud.", "...and keep their stools warm at the tavern. They'll want them back.", "That's the most hopeful thing anyone's said all week. I'll drink to it."},
      {"What's the strangest thing you've seen in a city square?", "A goblin auctioning 'genuine dragon eggs.' They were painted gourds. He made forty gold.", "A fully armored knight playing hopscotch on a chalk grid. Very seriously. On his way to war.", "Two bards turned a song into a duel. The crowd took sides. Beautiful chaos.", "A street preacher's been shouting about the end times for a week. The end times are taking their time.", "A stray dog adopted the entire city guard. They take turns feeding it. It eats better than I do.", "An apprentice mage misfired a portal and dropped straight into the sewers. We've all been there.", "A noble's carriage stuck in the market crowd, so he had to walk like the rest of us. The street rejoiced.", "A tauren gently lifting a lost gnome onto his shoulder so the little one could find his friends. Made my year.", "...this city is a circus with a war on the side, and I love every cobblestone of it.", "Couldn't have said it better. Same time tomorrow at the fountain?"},
      {"Settle a bar bet for us: hardest %boss% ever put down?", "%boss%, no contest. We threw ourselves at it for a whole %season%.", "Soft. Try it at %difficulty% with a pickup group and %consumable% running low.", "You're both wrong. The hard part was the trash before %boss%, not the boss.", "The hard part is always the %class% who stands in the fire. Every group has one.", "...we ARE the %class% who stands in the fire, aren't we.", "To standing in the fire. May we one day learn to step out of it.", "Drinks at %shop%. We've earned the wipe stories."},
      {"If you could own one thing in all Azeroth, what'd it be?", "%item%. I'd never set it down, not even to sleep.", "%mount%. Ride into %city% on that and you never pay for a drink again.", "Pfft. The title '%pvptitle%'. You can't buy what you bleed for.", "%gold% in the bank and a quiet cottage in %zone%. That's the dream.", "Exalted with every %rep% there is. Just to say I did it.", "...all of you chasing legends, and here's me just wanting a stall that sells out by %timeofday%.", "Honestly? That's the wisest answer at this table.", "To small dreams, then. They're the only ones that come true."},
      {"What's the worst luck you've had on a drop?", "Ran %instance% every week for a %season% and %boss% never once gave up %item%.", "Lost %item% to a %class% on a single dice roll. Off by one number.", "Sold a green for %gold%, then watched it resell for ten times that an hour later.", "Tracked %rare% across half of %zone%, dismounted to loot, and a passing %class% sniped it.", "...we are a table of the unluckiest souls in %city%, aren't we.", "And yet here we all are, still rolling. Still hoping.", "That's adventuring, friend. The Light gives, the dice take."},
    },
  },

  alliance = {
    -- standalone one-liners (single speaker)
    lines = {
      "Cathedral Square is quiet this morning. The Bishop's sermon must have run long again.",
      "Anyone else stop to watch the Stormwind guards change shift at the Trade District gates? Best free show in the city.",
      "The smell of fresh bread from the Trade District bakery is the only buff I need today.",
      "Pickpockets in Old Town again. Keep a hand on your coin purse near the Slaughtered Lamb crowd, friends.",
      "Sitting by the Stormwind canals watching the boats. Days like this make the wars feel far away.",
      "Mage Quarter portals are down again. Whoever's on duty, the line is out to the fountain.",
      "Just adopted a cat from the Cathedral district. Named him Bolvar. He judges everyone.",
      "Selling fresh-cut tulips from the Stormwind gardens! Brighten your keep, three silver a bunch.",
      "A fine day for a stroll through the Dwarven District. The forges are warm and the ale is warmer.",
      "Lost in the tram tunnels between Ironforge and Stormwind. Send a map. And a snack.",
      "They keep the Great Forge burning so bright you forget it's snowing in Dun Morogh.",
      "Sat by the Darnassus ponds and lost an hour to the moonlight on the water. No regrets.",
      "A Sentinel told me the leaves of Teldrassil never truly stop whispering. I believe her.",
      "The owls of Darnassus hooted all night. Either an omen or they're just owls. Probably owls.",
      "The crystals of the Exodar sing when the light hits them right. The draenei call it home now.",
      "The Exodar still tilts a little where it crashed. They say you get your sea legs eventually.",
      "Anchorites at the Exodar bless travelers for free. Took the blessing, felt great, fell off a ramp anyway.",
      "Made the full tour today: Stormwind to Ironforge by tram, Ironforge to Darnassus by boat. My feet are retired.",
      "A new adventurer asked me how to get to Stormwind from the night elf lands. Friend, clear your afternoon.",
      "First snow in Dun Morogh and the whole of Ironforge smells like mulled cider. Best time of year.",
      "Stormwind in spring, the gardens in full bloom. Even the guards crack a smile.",
      "Autumn leaves drifting down off Teldrassil into the Darnassus ponds. Bittersweet and beautiful.",
      "The Mage Quarter at night is all blue light and quiet humming. Easy to forget there's a war on.",
      "Old Town never really sleeps. The rogues just change shifts with the night watch.",
      "The Trade District at high noon is pure chaos. Auctioneers, beggars, nobles, and me, hopelessly lost.",
      "Cathedral District is the only quiet corner of Stormwind. I go there just to hear myself think.",
      "Two elves slow-dancing by the Darnassus moonwell while a bard played. The whole square went quiet.",
      "An anchorite blessed my journey and meant it. You can tell when someone means it.",
      "Anyone up for a scavenger hunt in Stormwind? First clue is 'Where the King's Shadow Lies.'",
      "Forming a casual band at the Stormwind gates, bound for %instance%. No pressure, just good company.",
      "Looking for a few brave souls at the Ironforge gates for a run to %instance%. Beards optional.",
      "Standing at the Darnassus portal forever. Is ANYONE going to %zone% today?",
      "The Stormwind fountain is NOT a wishing well, a swimming pool, OR a bath, and yet here we all are.",
      "Stormwind's spires catch the morning light like they're made of it. Pride of the Alliance, and rightly so.",
      "Ironforge has stood since before the stories started. Let the surface squabble; the mountain endures.",
      "Found a bookshop tucked behind the Mage Quarter. Smells of dust and old magic. I may never leave.",
      "Eyes open near Old Town tonight. Word is the thieves' guild is feeling ambitious. Aren't they always.",
      "A %race% %class% rode into the Trade District on %mount% and the gnome children lost their minds. Can't blame them.",
      "The %profession% trainer in Ironforge says she'll teach me to craft %item% one day. One VERY distant day.",
      "Cathedral's blessing every soldier bound for %zone% this %timeofday%. The Light go with them, every one.",
      "Some %level% %class% asked the way to %zone% in the Mage Quarter. Took the portal mage twenty minutes to stop laughing.",
      "Heard a Stormwind veteran earned '%pvptitle%' on the Wintergrasp wall. Bought him a pint at the Pig and Whistle and just listened.",
      "LFM %instance% %difficulty% forming at the Stormwind gates. Need a %role%, %gearscore%+, bring %consumable%.",
      "Saw a Sentinel back from %zone% with %item% still wet from the fight. Darnassus turned out just to watch her pass.",
      "Hit revered with %rep% today. The Ironforge quartermaster finally smiled at me. First time in a %season%.",
      "%weather% over Dun Morogh this %timeofday%. The tram's running slow and the whole of Ironforge smells of wet beard.",
      "A dwarf at the Stonefire Tavern swears he wrestled %rare% in the Hinterlands. Sober, he tells it shorter.",
    },
    -- two-person back-and-forth (speakers alternate A / B)
    duos = {
      {"The Lion's Pride Inn is packed tonight.", "It's the bard. He actually learned a second song.", "Two whole songs? Practically a symphony."},
      {"Why is there a gnome statue in the middle of Stormwind?", "Knowledge, valor, and exceptionally good engineering, my friend.", "It's so we always look up to the little folk."},
      {"Anyone know why the Ironforge gryphons look so smug?", "They get to leave whenever they want. Wouldn't you be smug?"},
      {"Best enchanter in the city? Asking for my very plain weapon.", "Old elf in the Mage Quarter. Charges a fortune, glows like a star.", "Worth it. My sword now has a personality."},
      {"Did you see the lights over the Mage Quarter last night?", "Probably an apprentice's experiment.", "It spelled out a name. THAT'S not an experiment."},
      {"First day with the city guard. Any tips?", "Stand up straight, learn the streets, and never chase a rogue into Old Town alone.", "Also the Mage Quarter sells the good coffee. You'll need it."},
      {"They say the King's planning another push north.", "Then Light help the lads who march. Icecrown takes more than it gives back.", "...I'll keep a candle lit in the Cathedral for them.", "We all will."},
      {"Teldrassil feels heavier lately, doesn't it?", "The Sentinels say the wilds are troubled. The leaves whisper louder.", "Or it's just the wind.", "...in ten thousand years, has it ever been 'just the wind' here?"},
      {"Did you catch that %race% %class% wielding %item% in the Trade District?", "Off %boss%, no less. %difficulty%.", "...and here's me still saving %gold% for a decent %profession% recipe."},
      {"%weather% over Dun Morogh again. The tram's crawling.", "Take %route% instead?", "In this %season%? I'd sooner wait. Pull up a stool at %shop% and we'll outlast it."},
      {"Exalted with %rep% at last. The %mount% is mine.", "How long did THAT take?", "Most of a %season% and more repair %gold% than I'll ever admit to my spouse."},
    },
    -- group discussions (many voices, rotating cast of 4-6)
    groups = {
      {"Which corner of Stormwind is the best to just sit and waste an afternoon?", "The canals, no contest. Watch the boats, feed the gulls, forget the war exists.", "Cathedral Square. Quietest spot in the whole city. I go there to think.", "The Trade District, if you like chaos. Best people-watching in the Alliance.", "Old Town, if you don't mind the company. The rooftops at dusk are something else.", "The Dwarven District. Warm forge, cold ale, and a dwarf who'll tell you his whole life story.", "...you've all forgotten the gardens in the Mage Quarter in spring.", "Light, you're right. The gardens. Lost a whole afternoon there last week.", "That's the secret, isn't it. This city's full of corners worth losing an afternoon to."},
      {"LFM %instance% %difficulty%, summon's at the Stormwind gates.", "Need what?", "A %role% and a %class% who knows the %boss% fight.", "%gearscore% and I've got %consumable% for the whole run.", "Invite's up. Mind the Cathedral bells, we move when they toll."},
      {"Worth grinding %rep% out of Ironforge?", "The %mount% alone is worth more than %gold%, aye.", "And the %profession% recipes you can't get anywhere else.", "Then I'll run the dailies till my gryphon knows the way by heart.", "It will. Mine flies to the quartermaster without me even asking."},
      {"That %race% %class% by the fountain — is that really %item%?", "Glows like Teldrassil at moonrise. Has to be.", "Earned it off %boss%, I heard. %difficulty%, no deaths.", "...I need to sit down. Some people just live a different life.", "Buy them a drink at the Lion's Pride. Greatness rubs off, they say.", "Nothing's ever rubbed off on you but ale stains.", "And I wear them with pride."},
      {"Best corner of the Alliance to watch %weather% roll in?", "The Stormwind canals. Rain on the water, lamps coming on one by one.", "The high terraces of Darnassus. You're above the clouds half the time.", "Ironforge — you don't watch the weather, you escape it by the Great Forge.", "The Exodar crystals catch storm-light like nothing else in the world.", "...all of you, romantics, the lot of you.", "It's a %season% evening and there's a war on. Let us have the small beauties.", "Fair. To small beauties, then. And to surviving long enough to notice them."},
    },
  },

  horde = {
    -- standalone one-liners (single speaker)
    lines = {
      "Valley of Strength is roaring today. Half the Horde came to gawk at the new recruits.",
      "The Drag smells of leather and smoke and something I'd rather not name. Home sweet home.",
      "Down in the Cleft of Shadow the warlocks are at it again. Whole tunnel reeks of brimstone.",
      "Garrosh's banners are everywhere now. The old guard mutters, but quietly.",
      "Zeppelin to the Undercity is late again. Goblin pilot says it's 'weather.' There is no weather up there.",
      "The Valley of Honor forges never sleep. Neither do the smiths, apparently.",
      "Grommash Hold is busy. When the Warchief calls a meeting, the whole city listens at the door.",
      "The wind on the rises of Thunder Bluff carries the smell of sage and open plains. Peace, finally.",
      "Watched the sun set over Mulgore from the highest rise. The tauren were right to settle here.",
      "Spirit Rise is quiet today. Even the totems seem to be listening for something.",
      "The Apothecarium's fumes are thick today. The Forsaken are brewing something that bubbles green.",
      "Undercity's canals run with things best left unexamined. The Forsaken call it 'ambiance.'",
      "A Forsaken bard played a dirge in the Trade Quarter. Saddest thing I've heard. Tipped him double.",
      "The Royal Quarter is colder than the grave. Fitting, given the tenants.",
      "Dark Rangers patrol the upper ring tonight. The Banshee Queen takes no chances.",
      "Silvermoon City gleams red and gold even at midnight. The blood elves spare no expense on beauty.",
      "The Royal Exchange is bustling. Blood elves haggle like it's an art form, because to them it is.",
      "Magisters arguing in Murder Row again. Yes, that's really what the street is called.",
      "A sin'dorei tailor offered to fix my robes. Now I'm too well-dressed to fight anything.",
      "Someone's lost a pet hawkstrider near the bank. Answers to 'Sparkles.' Reward offered, dignity not included.",
      "A Forsaken and a human stood at the same grave in Duskwood. Some losses don't pick a side.",
      "Took the zeppelin from Orgrimmar to the Undercity. Goblin pilot did a loop 'for fun.' I did not have fun.",
      "Spent the afternoon in Silvermoon just looking at the architecture. Felt underdressed the entire time.",
      "Thunder Bluff at dawn, Undercity at dusk. The Horde lands have a beauty the maps never capture.",
      "Summer heat in Orgrimmar is no joke. Even the orcs are seeking shade in the Drag today.",
      "Thunder over Thunder Bluff. On the nose, I know, but the tauren love it.",
      "The Cleft of Shadow gives me the creeps and I'm a warlock. That's saying something.",
      "Valley of Wisdom is where the old shaman gather. Walk soft and listen; they've earned their silence.",
      "The Pools of Vision in Thunder Bluff reflect the sky so clearly you forget which way is up.",
      "My hawkstrider knocked over a fruit cart in Silvermoon. The vendor charged me for 'street theater.'",
      "Trying to park my kodo by the Orgrimmar bank. Got a ticket. From a goblin. With a straight face.",
      "Say what you will about Orgrimmar, but watching the sun rise over those iron walls stirs something in the blood.",
      "Thunder Bluff doesn't conquer; it abides. There's a strength in that the warmongers never understand.",
      "Silvermoon rebuilt itself from ruin into the most beautiful city on Azeroth. Spite never looked so elegant.",
      "The Undercity is a tomb that learned to live. Grim, yes. But the Forsaken made a home where there was only grief.",
      "Word from Orgrimmar: the Warchief's recruiting for a march north. The old veterans sharpen their axes and say nothing.",
      "Gathering a war-band at the Orgrimmar gates for a strike on %instance%. Bring steel and a strong stomach.",
      "Anyone at the Thunder Bluff rise want to ride out to %zone%? The plains are calling and the city's too loud.",
      "A %race% %class% rode through the Valley of Strength on %mount% with %item% strapped to their back. Even the grunts stopped to %emote%.",
      "Word from the front: someone put %boss% in the dirt at %difficulty% and lived to brag about it in the Drag.",
      "LFM %instance% %difficulty% mustering at the Orgrimmar gates. Need a %role%, %gearscore%+, and bring your own %consumable%.",
      "The %profession% master in the Valley of Honor wants %gold% just to teach me %item%. The Earth Mother gives; the trainers most certainly take.",
      "Hit exalted with %rep% this %timeofday%. The quartermaster handed over the %mount% like it was nothing. Lok'tar earned, mon.",
      "Some %level% %class% wandered into the Cleft of Shadow asking for directions to %zone%. The warlocks just... smiled. Poor fool.",
      "A Forsaken hunter dragged %rare% back from %zone% to mount on the wall. The Apothecarium offered to 'preserve' it. She declined, wisely.",
      "%weather% over the Barrens on %route% this %timeofday%. The wind riders are grounded and the caravan masters are furious.",
      "Heard a veteran in Grommash Hold carries the title '%pvptitle%'. Earned it the only way the Horde respects — in blood.",
      "Bard in the Undercity sang of %tale% till the whole Trade Quarter went still. Even the Forsaken remembered how to mourn.",
    },
    -- two-person back-and-forth (speakers alternate A / B)
    duos = {
      {"Why does every orc in Orgrimmar look like they could bench-press a kodo?", "Because most of us can.", "The kodos volunteer. It's a status thing."},
      {"How do you not fall off Thunder Bluff? It's all cliffs and rope bridges.", "We don't look down. The Earth Mother handles the rest."},
      {"Does it ever bother you that the Undercity used to be Lordaeron's crown jewel?", "Every single day. That's rather the point."},
      {"Everything in Silvermoon is so perfect it's almost unsettling.", "Ten thousand years of refinement, darling. Try to keep up."},
      {"The Warchief's banners went up overnight. All of them.", "Garrosh doesn't do subtle.", "...think the old guard will say anything?", "Quietly. Always quietly. That's how you keep your head."},
      {"A shaman told me the elements are angry lately.", "Aye. The earth's been restless under Orgrimmar for weeks.", "Omen?", "Or the forges. Hard to say. The old ones say omen. I'd listen to the old ones."},
      {"Caught a Forsaken laughing in the Apothecarium today.", "Now THAT'S unsettling. What was so funny?", "Didn't ask. Some questions you don't want answered in the Undercity.", "Wise. Very wise."},
      {"That %race% %class% in the Valley of Strength is carrying %item%.", "Off %boss%, at %difficulty%. Earned it in blood.", "...and I'm still hauling ore for %gold% a stack. The Earth Mother tests us all differently."},
      {"%weather% grounded the wind riders again.", "So we take %route%?", "In this %season%? We drink at %shop% till it clears, mon. The Barrens isn't going anywhere."},
      {"Hit exalted with %rep% this %timeofday%.", "The %mount%?", "Mine at last. And every %profession% pattern they were hoarding. Lok'tar, it was worth the grind."},
    },
    -- group discussions (many voices, rotating cast of 4-6)
    groups = {
      {"Which Horde city actually feels like home to you?", "Orgrimmar. Iron walls, hot forges, and the sunrise over the gates. Nothing like it.", "Thunder Bluff. Open sky, clean wind, totems humming. The plains heal you.", "Silvermoon, obviously. Beauty rebuilt from ash. We earned every gilded arch.", "The Undercity. I know, I know. But the Forsaken made a home out of nothing. That means something.", "Sen'jin and the echoes of the islands, for me. The drums still call us, mon.", "...the orc and the tauren are about to argue forges versus plains again, aren't they?", "We always do. And we always end up drinking together after.", "That's the Horde, isn't it. Different blood, same fire.", "Lok'tar. To home, whatever shape it takes."},
      {"War-band's short for %instance% %difficulty%.", "Short what?", "A %role% and a %class% who won't bolt when %boss% enrages.", "%gearscore% here, and I've %consumable% enough for the lot of you.", "Then strap in. We ride from the Orgrimmar gates at %timeofday%. Lok'tar."},
      {"Is %rep% worth the grind, honestly?", "The %mount% at exalted is worth more than %gold% to a Silvermoon collector, so aye.", "And the %profession% patterns. You'll not find %item% taught anywhere else.", "Then it's settled. Dailies at dawn till the quartermaster knows my name.", "He'll know it. He knew mine before I knew the way back to Orgrimmar."},
      {"That %race% %class% in the Drag is carrying %item%, I swear it.", "Off %boss%? At %difficulty%?", "Glows like Silvermoon at midnight. Has to be real.", "Or the best forgery a goblin ever sold. Half the Drag is forgeries.", "...only one way to know. Buy them a drink and ask.", "In the Drag? You buy a stranger a drink, you wake up missing a kidney, mon.", "...fair. We admire from a safe distance, then."},
      {"Best place in the Horde to watch %weather% come in?", "The high rises of Thunder Bluff. You're up in it before it ever touches the plain.", "The Orgrimmar walls at %timeofday%. Iron and storm-light, nothing finer.", "The spires of Silvermoon. Even a downpour looks like a painting from up there.", "...the Undercity. No weather at all. That IS the appeal, for some of us.", "Leave it to the Forsaken to call 'no sky' a feature.", "We made peace with the dark a long time ago. You'd be surprised how restful it is.", "To each their own horizon, then. Drinks in the Valley of Honor after?", "Lok'tar. First round's on the one who said Undercity."},
    },
  },

